Description: Amsc ASA, previously known as American Shipping Company ASA, is a Norway-based ship owning company. The business model of AMSC is to own and bareboat charter out U.S. built vessels to qualified U.S. citizen operators, making the Company a pure play Jones Act owner. The objective of the business model is to generate a stable and predictable cash flow from long term bareboat leases protected from short term market fluctuations, with upside potential through profit sharing arrangements with the charterers. The Company owns nine modern handy size product tankers and one modern handy size shuttle tanker, all built at Philly Shipyard (PHLY), which is a U.S. shipyard. The Company s headquartered in Lysaker, Norway, with its principal operating subsidiaries located in Pennsylvania, USA.
